name: Friedrich_Weyerhaeuser
text:
Friedrich Weyerhaeuser
Friedrich Weyerhaeuser was a lumber baron who purchased one million acres of forest from the Northern Pacific Railroad, establishing a timber industry in Washington.
Behind the scenes
Friedrich Weyerhäuser (November 21, 1834 – April 4, 1914) was a German-American timber mogul and founder of the Weyerhaeuser Company.
